Description: Sherd from base of pottery closed vase; low ring foot. Rather coarse micaceous clay. Very worn. Outside slipped white with dark band on outside of foot. Graffito inscription under foot.
Bibliographic references: Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (p. 171, no. 64)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.2224)
